# README Sync

After making any change that affects content documented in `README.md`, update the README in the same response.

## Triggers — update README when you change:

| What changed | What to update in README |
|---|---|
| `package.json` scripts | Scripts table |
| `package.json` dependencies | Stack table (if a new major dep) |
| New file/directory in `app/`, `components/`, `lib/`, `scripts/`, `content/` | Project Structure section |
| New API route (`app/api/*/route.ts`) | Project Structure + AI Features (if AI-related) |
| New env variable or `.env.local.example` | Prerequisites table |
| `content/projects.ts`, `content/skills.ts`, `content/bio.ts` | Content section if the editing workflow changes |
| Roadmap phase completed | Roadmap checklist — check off the phase |
| `scripts/generate-embeddings.ts` or seed workflow changes | Scripts table + seed instructions |

## What NOT to update

- Internal implementation details (function names, types, logic)
- Files that don't change the developer or user workflow
- Minor refactors with no user-facing impact

## Format rules

- Keep the README factual and concise — no marketing language
- Code blocks must be copy-pasteable and tested
- The Scripts table must always match the actual `package.json` scripts exactly
